'''Durai Sundar''' is an Indian computational biologist, bioinformatician and an associate professor at the Department of Biochemical Engineering and Biotechnology of the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Delhi]]. He is known for his studies in the fields of [[genome editing]] tool designing, biological studies of natural drugs and [[metabolic engineering]] as well as for his participation in the Indo-Japanese collaborative research initiatives on anti-cancer drug development and is a life member of the [[National Academy of Sciences, India]]. The [[Department of Biotechnology]] of the Government of India awarded him the [[National Bioscience Award for Career Development]], one of the highest Indian science awards, for his contributions to biosciences, in 2012.

== Biography ==
[[File:Dpt.bt.png|thumb|left|Department of Biotechnology - Pondicherry University]]
Durai Sundar, born in the south Indian state of [[Pondicherry]], did his undergraduate and post-graduate studies as well as his doctoral studies at [[Pondicherry University]] and completed his post-doctoral work at [[Johns Hopkins University]].<ref name="Biosketch on IITD">{{Cite web |url=http://web.iitd.ac.in/~sundar/biosketch.html |title=Biosketch on IITD |date=2018-02-01 |website=web.iitd.ac.in |access-date=2018-02-01}}</ref> Subsequently, he joined the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Delhi]] (IITD) as a member of faculty where he is an associate professor, holding the Dupont Young Professor chair.<ref name="D. Sundar - IIT Delhi - Biochemical Engineering and Biotechnology">{{Cite web |url=http://beb.iitd.ac.in/sundar.html |title=D. Sundar - IIT Delhi - Biochemical Engineering and Biotechnology |date=2018-02-01 |website=beb.iitd.ac.in |access-date=2018-02-01}}</ref> At IITD, he chairs [[Tryst, IIT Delhi]] and serves as an associate faculty at the School of Interdisciplinary Research and the Value Education Centre (NRCVEE). He also coordinates the Bioinformatics Centre, a project funded by the [[Department of Biotechnology]] and DaiLab, a collaborative  biomedical initiative between IIT Delhi and the [[National Institute of Advanced Industrial Science and Technology]] (AIST, Japan).<ref name="Faculty profile">{{Cite web |url=http://web.iitd.ac.in/~sundar/ |title=Faculty profile |date=2018-02-01 |website=web.iitd.ac.in |access-date=2018-02-01}}</ref><ref name="IIT Delhi inaugurates DAILAB international laboratory for Advanced Biomedicine ">{{Cite web |url=http://www.dbtindia.nic.in/iit-delhi-innaugurates-dailab-international-laboratory-for-advanced-biomedicine/ |title=IIT Delhi innaugurates DAILAB international laboratory for Advanced Biomedicine |date=2018-02-01 |website=www.dbtindia.nic.in |access-date=2018-02-01}}</ref>

== Professional profile ==
[[File:Withania somnifera00.jpg|thumb|Ashwagandha flower]]
Sundar is known to have carried out research in the fields of [[genome editing]] tool designing, biological studies of natural drugs and [[metabolic engineering]].<ref name="Faculty profile" /> When DaiLab was established at IIT Delhi, he became the coordinator of the initiative.<ref name="Japan & India step up ties in the field of Science & Technology">{{Cite press release |title=Japan & India step up ties in the field of Science & Technology |date=2015 |publisher=Embassy of Japan in India |location=Japan |url=http://www.in.emb-japan.go.jp/Press_Releases_Embassy/PR_DAILAB_2015.pdf}}</ref> He was a part of the team which studied the anti-cancer properties of [[Withania somnifera]], commonly known as Ashwagandha, and the team identified [[Withanolide]], [[Withaferin A]] and Withanone as the three steroidal contents of the plant which gives the property to it;<ref name="Ashwagandha has capacity to deal with complicated cancers, finds research">{{Cite news |url=https://www.biovoicenews.com/ashwagandha-capacity-deal-complicated-cancers-finds-research/ |title=Ashwagandha has capacity to deal with complicated cancers, finds research |last=Correspondent |first=BioVoice |date=2017-04-28 |work=BioVoiceNews |access-date=2018-02-01 |language=en-US}}</ref> they published their findings by way of an article published in Cell Death and Disease journal in 2017.<ref name="Withaferin-A kills cancer cells with and without telomerase: chemical, computational and experimental evidences">{{Cite journal |last=Yu |first=Yue |last2=Katiyar |first2=Shashank P |last3=Sundar |first3=Durai |last4=Kaul |first4=Zeenia |last5=Miyako |first5=Eijiro |last6=Zhang |first6=Zhenya |last7=Kaul |first7=Sunil C |last8=Reddel |first8=Roger R |last9=Wadhwa |first9=Renu |date=April 2017 |title=Withaferin-A kills cancer cells with and without telomerase: chemical, computational and experimental evidences |url=http://www.nature.com/articles/cddis201733 |journal=Cell Death & Disease |language=En |volume=8 |issue=4 |pages=e2755–e2755 |doi=10.1038/cddis.2017.33 |issn=2041-4889}}</ref> His studies have been documented by way of a number of articles<ref name="On Google Scholar">{{Cite web |url=https://scholar.google.co.in/citations?user=s1pREqwAAAAJ |title=On Google Scholar |date=2018-01-30 |publisher=Google Scholar |access-date=2018-01-30}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Please see ''Selected bibliography'' section}} and [[ResearchGate]], an online repository of scientific articles has listed 80 of them.<ref name="On ResearchGate">{{Cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Durai_Sundar |title=On ResearchGate |date=2018-01-30 |publisher=On ResearchGate |access-date=2018-01-30}}</ref> Besides, he has contributed chapters to books published by others.<ref name="KaulWadhwa2017">{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=c7I1DwAAQBAJ&pg=PA263 |title=Science of Ashwagandha: Preventive and Therapeutic Potentials |last=Sunil C. Kaul |last2=Renu Wadhwa |date=13 September 2017 |publisher=Springer |isbn=978-3-319-59192-6 |pages=263}}</ref><ref name="SinghDhar2014">{{cite book|author1=Vikram Singh|author2=Pawan K. Dhar|title=Systems and Synthetic Biology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eYDZBQAAQBAJ&pg=PR11|date=15 December 2014|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-94-017-9514-2|pages=11–}}</ref> He has also delivered invited speeches at international seminars and conferences<ref name="2014-2015 Seminars-  IIIT-Delhi">{{Cite web |url=https://old.iiitd.ac.in/research/seminar/2014-15 |title=2014-2015 Seminars-  IIIT-Delhi |date=2018-02-01 |website=old.iiitd.ac.in |language=en |access-date=2018-02-01}}</ref> which included the DAILAB PIKNIKH SERIES V seminar held at [[Tsukuba]], Japan in 2015.<ref name="DAILAB PIKNIKH SERIES V">{{Cite web |url=https://unit.aist.go.jp/bmd/en/event/pdf/AIST-IIT%20Symposium%2018th%20June%202015.pdf |title=DAILAB PIKNIKH SERIES V |date=2018-02-01 |website=National Institute of Advanced Industrial Science and Technology |access-date=2018-02-01}}</ref>

== Awards and honors ==
Sundar received the Swarna Jayanti Award of the [[National Academy of Sciences, India]] in 2005<ref name="The National Academy of Sciences, India - Awardees">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nasi.org.in/sjp.htm |title=The National Academy of Sciences, India - Awardees |date=2018-02-01 |website=www.nasi.org.in |access-date=2018-02-01}}</ref> and three honors in 2006, the Young Scientist Award and the Innovative Young Biotechnologist Award of the [[Department of Science and Technology (India)|Department of Science and Technology]]<ref name="Awards and Honors">{{Cite web |url=http://web.iitd.ac.in/~sundar/awards.html |title=Awards and Honors |date=2018-02-01 |website=web.iitd.ac.in |access-date=2018-02-01}}</ref> as well as the Young Scientist Award of the [[Indian Science Congress Association]].<ref name="13 receive Young Scientist Award at ISC">{{Cite news |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india/13-receive-young-scientist-award-at-isc/story-yWajPSEZSakMMCvVerMafK.html |title=13 receive Young Scientist Award at ISC |date=2006-01-05 |work=Hindustan Times |access-date=2018-02-01 |language=en}}</ref> The [[Indian National Science Academy]] awarded him the INSA Medal for Young Scientists in 2008<ref name="INSA Young Scientist Medal">{{Cite web |url=https://www.insaindia.res.in/youngmedal.php |title=INSA Young Scientist Medal |date=2018-02-01 |website=www.insaindia.res.in |access-date=2018-02-01}}</ref> and the Lady Tata Memorial Trust selected him for the Young Researcher Award in 2011; the same year as he was elected as a life member of the National Academy of Sciences, India.<ref name="The National Academy of Sciences, India - Life Members">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nasi.org.in/lifemem.asp?RsFilter=S |title=The National Academy of Sciences, India - Life Members |date=2018-02-01 |website=www.nasi.org.in |access-date=2018-02-01}}</ref> The [[Department of Biotechnology]] (DBT) of the Government of India awarded him the [[National Bioscience Award for Career Development]], one of the highest Indian science awards in 2012.<ref name="Awardees of National Bioscience Awards for Career Development">{{Cite web |url=http://dbtindia.nic.in/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/list_of_bioscience_awardees.pdf |title=Awardees of National Bioscience Awards for Career Development |date=2016 |publisher=Department of Biotechnology |access-date=2017-11-20}}</ref> He received two more awards in 2013, the Young Scientist Award of the Asian Biophysics Association<ref name="Awards and Honors" /> and the Prof. Umakant Sinha Memorial Award of the Indian Science Congress Association.<ref name="Prof. Umakant Sinha Memorial Award">{{Cite web |url=http://www.sciencecongress.nic.in/isca_awardees_2012-13.php |title=Prof. Umakant Sinha Memorial Award |date=2018-02-01 |website=www.sciencecongress.nic.in |access-date=2018-02-01}}</ref>

