{{Main|Music-related memory}}

In [[music]], '''tonal memory''' or "aural recall" is the ability to recall a previously sounded [[pitch (music)|tone]].{{huh?|Ungrammatical. A previously sounded *what* with tone?|date=October 2017}}<ref>Gorow, Ron (2002). ''Hearing and Writing Music: Professional Training for Today's Musician (2nd Edition)''. {{ISBN|978-0-9629496-7-8}}.</ref> Tonal memory assists with  [[musical aptitude|staying in tune]] and may be developed through [[ear training]]. Extensive tonal memory may be recognized as an indication of potential [[Musical composition|compositional]] ability.<ref>Haroutounian, Joanne (2002). ''Kindling the Spark : Recognizing and Developing Musical Talent''. {{ISBN|978-0-19-512948-9}}.</ref>

Tonal memory may be used as a strategy for learning to identify musical tones absolutely.  Although those who attempt the strategy believe they are learning [[absolute pitch]], the ability thus is generally not musically relevant,<ref name="Bachem, 1940">{{cite journal | author = Bachem, A. | year=1940 | title=The genesis of absolute pitch | journal=Journal of the Acoustical Society of America | volume=11 | pages=434–439 | doi = 10.1121/1.1916056 | issue = 4}}</ref> and their absolute tonal memory declines substantially or completely over time if not constantly reinforced.<ref name="Meyer, 1899">{{cite journal | author = Meyer, M. | year=1899 | title=Is the memory of absolute pitch capable of development by training? | journal=Psychological Review | volume=6 | pages=514–516 | doi = 10.1037/h0069034 | issue = 5}}[http://www.aruffo.com/eartraining/research/articles/meyer99.htm Full text]</ref> Short term memory can also play a role with tonal memory as well. To figure out what the tones/pitches in a phrase are either similar or different. Having the memory to recall the pitches will help make the distinction.<ref name=":1">{{cite web|last1=Deutsch|first1=Diana|title=Short Term Memory for Tones|url=http://deutsch.ucsd.edu/psychology/pages.php?i=209|website=DianaDeutsch|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref>

